{"name": "ridgespace", "metadata": {"name": "RidgeSpace", "version": "0.1.6", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "License :: OSI Approved :: GNU General Public License v3 (GPLv3)", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Topic :: Scientific/Engineering :: Bio-Informatics"], "home_page": "http://pypi.python.org/pypi/RidgeSpace/", "license": "GPL", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["matplotlib", "numpy", "pandas", "scipy"], "summary": "Unravelling three-dimensionally dynamics of spatial multi-modal data", "upload_time": 1733906459}, "documentation": ["## Unravelling three-dimensionally dynamics of spatial multi-modal data with RidgeSpace\r\n\r\nYou can freely use RidgeSpace for illustrating, comparing, and tracking the spatial dynamics of molecular signals.\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\">\r\n  <img src='./docs/RidgeSpace.png'>\r\n</p>\r\n<p align=\"center\">\r\n  Overview of RidgeSpace.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n### Prerequisites\r\n\r\n    \"matplotlib\", \"numpy\", \"pandas\", \"scipy\"\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nI suggest that you can freely install RidgeSpace with pip. \r\n\r\n```bash\r\npip install RidgeSpace\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou can also use a separate conda environment for installing RidgeSpace.\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nconda create -y -n RidgeSpace_env python=3.7\r\nsource activate RidgeSpace_env\r\npip install RidgeSpace\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Basic Examples\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\">\r\n  <img src='./docs/Examples.png'>\r\n</p>\r\n<p align=\"center\">\r\n  Examples of RidgeSpace.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\nTest data and code for RidgeSpace provided in the \"tests\" folder.\r\n\r\nSingle-gene spatial depiction:\r\n```bash\r\nRidgeSpace.pl_single(adata, plot_name = 'Mbp', obs_cluster='Clusters', elev=40, view=160))\r\n```\r\n\r\nMulti-modal spatial comparison:\r\n```bash\r\nRidgeSpace.pl_multipleOUT(adata, plot_nameA = 'Tnnt1', plot_nameB = 'Tnnt2', obs_cluster='Clusters', elev=20, view=160, plot_HE_bg=True)\r\n```\r\n\r\nPseudotime spatial trajectory representation:\r\n```bash\r\nRidgeSpace.pl_trajectory(adata, plot_name = 'Pseudotime', obs_cluster='Clusters', elev=45, view=165, HE_z=10)\r\n```\r\n\r\nFurther tutorials please refer to  https://RidgeSpace.readthedocs.io/.\r\n\r\n\r\n"], "modules": [{"name": "RidgeSpace.version", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "RidgeSpace.version.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "RidgeSpace", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "RidgeSpace.convert_zarr", "xref": {"fqname": "RidgeSpace.main.convert_zarr", "project": null}}, {"name": "RidgeSpace.pl_multipleIN", "xref": {"fqname": "RidgeSpace.main.pl_multipleIN", "project": null}}, {"name": "RidgeSpace.pl_multipleOUT", "xref": {"fqname": "RidgeSpace.main.pl_multipleOUT", "project": null}}, {"name": "RidgeSpace.pl_single", "xref": {"fqname": "RidgeSpace.main.pl_single", "project": null}}, {"name": "RidgeSpace.pl_trajectory", "xref": {"fqname": "RidgeSpace.main.pl_trajectory", "project": null}}, {"name": "RidgeSpace.tl_denoise", "xref": {"fqname": "RidgeSpace.main.tl_denoise", "project": null}}, {"name": "RidgeSpace.tl_HE", "xref": {"fqname": "RidgeSpace.main.tl_HE", "project": null}}, {"name": "RidgeSpace.tl_mesh", "xref": {"fqname": "RidgeSpace.main.tl_mesh", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "RidgeSpace.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "RidgeSpace.utils.plot_Ridge", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "ax", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "norm", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "vmin", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "vmax", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "lightsource", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Create a 3D RidgeSpace plot.\n\nParameters\n----------\nX, Y, Z : 2D arrays\n    Data values.\n\nrcount, ccount : int\n    Maximum number of samples used in each direction.  If the input\n    data is larger, it will be downsampled (by slicing) to these\n    numbers of points.  Defaults to 50.\n\ncmap : Colormap\n    Colormap of the surface patches.\n\nfacecolors : array-like of colors.\n    Colors of each individual patch.\n\nnorm : Normalize\n    Normalization for the colormap.\n\nvmin, vmax : float\n    Bounds for the normalization.\n\nshade : bool, default: True\n    Whether to shade the facecolors.  Shading is always disabled when\n    *cmap* is specified.\n\nlightsource : `~matplotlib.colors.LightSource`\n    The lightsource to use when *shade* is True."]}, {"name": "RidgeSpace.utils.color_variant", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "hex_color", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "brightness_offset", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["takes a color like #87c95f and produces a lighter or darker variant "]}, {"name": "RidgeSpace.utils.adjust_lightness_batch", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "rgb_array", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "amount", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "RidgeSpace.utils.adjust_lightness", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "color", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "amount", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "RidgeSpace.utils.rgb2gray", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "rgb", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "RidgeSpace.utils.get_HE_mask", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "img_HE", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "scale", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []